                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please evaluate and fix\/categorize as necessary.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=wil",
                        "name": "wil",
                        "displayName": "Wil Sinclair",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-06-07T21:51:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-07T21:51:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23458",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hagerd",
                        "name": "hagerd",
                        "displayName": "Darien Hager",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Isn't the XML-RPC spec that i4\/int is a four-byte signed integer? The only way you're receiving or sending an integer > +2,147,483,647 is if the either you or the other end is breaking spec.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hagerd",
                        "name": "hagerd",
                        "displayName": "Darien Hager",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-08-12T12:04:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-08-12T12:04:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24437",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, all.\n\nI  think 2 solutions.\nDo you think which is better?\n\n1)\nThe Zend_XmlRpc_Value_Integer throws exception if the $value is bigger than 2 147 483 647 .\n\n2)\nWe will recommend to validate parameter before using Zend_XmlRpc_Value_Integer  in reference manual.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-11T04:09:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-11T04:09:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31618",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=apex",
                        "name": "apex",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Brandenburg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I would suggest that an exception is thrown (option 1) as an big integer (within xmlrpc) is an i8 type not int or i4\n\n<int>2147483648<\/int> invalid (throw error)\n<i8>2147483648<\/i8> no problem its a big int the other side is telling me.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=apex",
                        "name": "apex",
                        "displayName": "Michiel Brandenburg",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-05T07:03:38.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-05T07:03:38.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33782",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've fixed this issue by just throwing an exception when an overlong integer is passed. I think supporting the non-standardized i8 element will be a good idea though, as it is implemented pretty widely. Resolved in r17753",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=lars",
                        "name": "lars",
                        "displayName": "Lars Strojny",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-08-22T09:12:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-08-22T09:12:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/33931",
